message: initial placeholder commit
PyCIBMA --> NiMARE
Add additional layer to meta classes and add new methods to dataset.Dataset.

Update README and fill in IBMA methods.

The IBMA methods are mostly Python translations of the MATLAB code in
the IBMA toolbox. Still not sure about the empirical null
distributions, and the MFX GLM is still empty.

Large update

- Add Dockerfile and script to create Dockerfile.
- Fix bug in nimare.meta.cbma.utils.compute_ma
- Add MFX GLM (still need to convert to workflow)
- Add multiple comparisons correction to IBMAs
    - Do not use FWE with empirical null distributions
- Truncate p-values in IBMAs with empirical null distributions before
converting to z-values
- Add dataset with sub peaks in coordinates
- Add t_to_z function from Dr. Vanessa Sochat’s TtoZ package (with
duecredit citations)
- Add new dependencies to version.py
Update contributing guidelines
Split ontology annotation and update README.
Update README with additional functionality
Add link to code of conduct to README.
Add skeleton for text2brain encoding.

Add CogAtLemmatizer and skeleton for text2brain.

- Reorganize annotation models into topic and vector models (was just
topic models before)
- GloVe model (word2brain) is a vector model (or whatever the
appropriate name is), not a topic model.

Add badges.

Given that CI, codecov, and RTD aren’t set up yet, these badges are
broken.
Change badge.
